

###Adding cURL command to Postman for use in Jenkins#########

###Select Import > Paste Raw Text
###Then choose Basic Auth and enter username and password in my case my API TOKEN
##And that should do it


#REF: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27957943/simulate-a-specific-curl-in-postman


##########SET CUSTOM CONTENT-TYPE###########################

###After selection Application/JSON under RAW for your 'Body'###########
##Click on "Headers" and in the 'Value' for Content-Type enter your custom Content-Type###
## Ex. application/vnd.api+json or whatever your API requires; this will change your content-type under RAW####
##To 'Text'
##REF: https://github.com/postmanlabs/postman-app-support/issues/1498
